&lt;h2 id="problem-description">Problem Description
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>The n-Queens problem involves placing $n$ queens on an $n \times n$ chessboard such that no two queens attack each other. This means no two queens can be in the same row, same column, or on the same diagonal (following standard chess queen movement rules).&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>